64,http://www.armslist.com/posts/242064,For Sale:  1967 Enfield 2A1 .308 nato 7.62x51,"Castle Rock, Denver, Colorado",$ 325,"Listed On: Friday, December 2, 2011",Rifles,no type,308/7.62 NATO                                                                                ,Bolt Action                                                                                ,Rifle,I have here a very nice Enfield 2A1 built by Ishapore in 1967. The caliber is .308 NATO. These are much more reasonable to shoot than the .303's being all that ammo dried up a few years back. The bore is beautiful on this being it probably never shot  corrosive ammo. I had originally bought this with the intention of turning it into a British Enfield 308 sniper clone but never got around to it and probably won't with all my other projects. It shoots very well and is quite fun. Most people on the range are usually surprised to see one of these in .308. Face to face with ID.
